<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-09-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/129.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Honduras</gloss>
                                to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa, Honduras</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-09-22"><hi rend="italic">September 22, 1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I am glad to answer Your Excellency’s courteous message of yesterday by
                            saying that I appreciate, to their high value, the good offices of Your
                            Excellency and the Most Excellent President of Mexico toward insuring
                            the maintenance of peace in Central America, and that I accept with the
                            greatest pleasure the invitation to the conference that is to meet in
                            Washington in November next and to which I will immediately appoint the
                            representatives of Honduras.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Miguel R.
                            Dávila.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>